claim.claim-text:
1. A non-contact process or method for measuring sebum or oil from skin or other substrate comprising: 
(1) choosing a desired spot on the body of a subject; 
(2) optionally cleansing said spot using cleansing wash, facial wash or alcoholic wipe in an amount adequate to remove all or part of sebum or oil; 
(3) applying fluorescent lipophilic dye to the spot where sebum or oil is to be measured; 
(4) illuminating the spot on said subject at the excitation wavelength of the fluorescent dye; and 
(5) collecting fluorescent emission at desired wavelength of the dye.
